>Review of Breaking the Ice (Queen) by ZZX

(CONTAINS SPOILERS)

First of all, for a first attempt serious creative writing, it's very good. Good description, doesn't get bogged down in too much detail and the illustrations are a nice touch. The dialogue is also good as I've seen many writers get it wrong.

Also I enjoy the fact the anthros have animal traits in regards to smell. Makes them feel different than humans.

Nice to see the main human character has a name. You didn't fall into the typical /hmofa/ writer's blunder of going with anon for the 1000th time. Good to see something refreshing.

But there are some improvements to be made.

The biggest flaw I found is the characters, specifically Alex.

I don't like her.

I knew she was going to warm up to Peanut at some point but I had trouble getting to like her. Beth is hatable in a good way being a bully and all but Alex is different. I found it hard to grow attached to her when she acts so rude and disrespectful to Peanut. Peanut is alright but I feel his 'pee pants' backstory and kiss should have been saved for a later moment. Perhaps instead having it that instead of kissing Alex, Alex just begin inhaling his scent to get off.

I would have saved the kiss and backstory for later to show how much him and Alex have grown as characters. Feels a bit too soon. But seeing you don't plan to continue it, it's forgivable as a short story.

Also some of the font doesn't match with the rest of the work, minor error but noticeable. I wasn't looking for spelling mistakes.

Apart from that, good work and happy writing. Hope to see more.

If you want a short story with a tsundere wolf and some nice art to go with it, I recommend this story.
